activity-description.narrative:
The activities are implemented at community level as well as in the “transitory spaces” hosting discharged patients called step down facilities and are composed of: 
	Rehabilitation care;
	Donation of assistive devices;
	Education of caregivers;
	Psychosocial support activities;
	Eventually complementary HEI (household essential items) in case the family of the person have not been targeted by global emergency distributions or additional items are required;
	The mapping of existing services allowing orientation/information of beneficiaries; 
	Sensitization, key messages diffusion, bilateral specific support to partners to improve inclusive practices and accessibility design of constructions through the setting up of an ITU (Inclusion Technical Unit).
